spec: uuid_extra162
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(uuid)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html — Python uuid module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/uuid.py"
    - "uuid_extra161.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.NAMESPACE_DNS/__NAMESPACE_URL class names / UUID.__dict__.__contains__ for __int__/__hash__/__eq__/__str__ / dunder name lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra160.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__ for hex/int/bytes/bytes_le/fields/time_low/version/variant (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra159.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.SafeUUID.__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__ ('Enum') / SafeUUID.safe.value==0 / SafeUUID.unsafe.value==-1 (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra158.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.uuid1/__uuid3/__uuid4/__uuid5 .__name__/__module__/__class__.__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra157.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__name__=='UUID' / UUID.__module__=='uuid' / UUID.__bases__[0].__name__=='object' / NAMESPACE_DNS/URL/OID/X500.__class__.__name__=='UUID' (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra156.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__dict__ property membership and meta-attributes (__len__()==37/__class__.__name__=='mappingproxy') (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid.zspec / early extras — cover uuid.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in uuid_extra86 through uuid_extra161."
    - "Wave 352 theme: uuid.UUID.__dict__ dunder membership for __init__/__new__/__repr__/__str__/__hash__/__eq__ and dict total length 37. uuid_extra161 anchors __int__/__str__/__hash__/__eq__ membership (via both table and standalone); uuid_extra161 anchors __repr__ as confirmed in its notes but does NOT anchor __repr__ membership via a table row or standalone. uuid_extra156 anchors __str__/__repr__ via 'in' syntax. This spec anchors __init__/__new__(False)/__repr__ membership and the __len__()==37 dict size as the primary novel content."
    - "uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__('__init__') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. UUID.__init__ sets up the UUID from its various input forms (hex/bytes/int/fields/version)."
    - "uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__('__new__') == False. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. UUID uses __init__ (not __new__) for instance creation — __new__ is NOT in UUID.__dict__."
    - "uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__('__repr__') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. UUID.__repr__ returns 'UUID(repr-string)'."
    - "uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__('__str__') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. (Confirmed; uuid_extra161 also anchors.)"
    - "uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__('__hash__') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. (Confirmed; uuid_extra161 also anchors.)"
    - "uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__('__eq__') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. (Confirmed; uuid_extra161 also anchors.)"
    - "uuid.UUID.__dict__.__len__() == 37. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. dict keys verified: ['__doc__', '__eq__', '__firstlineno__', '__ge__', '__getstate__', '__gt__', '__hash__', '__init__', '__int__', '__le__', '__lt__', '__module__', '__repr__', '__setattr__', '__setstate__', '__slots__', '__static_attributes__', '__str__', '__weakref__', '_from_int', 'bytes', 'bytes_le', 'clock_seq', 'clock_seq_hi_variant', 'clock_seq_low', 'fields', 'hex', 'int', 'is_safe', 'node', 'time', 'time_hi_version', 'time_low', 'time_mid', 'urn', 'variant', 'version'] — 37 total keys."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__('__new__') == False. UUID does not define __new__; instance creation uses __init__ alone. This contrasts with struct.Struct (which defines both __new__ and __init__ in its dict). '__new__'(7 chars) is NOT a key in UUID.__dict__ — novel anchor."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__('__init__') == True. UUID.__init__ accepts keyword arguments: hex, bytes, bytes_le, fields, int, version, is_safe. '__init__'(8 chars) IS a key in UUID.__dict__ — novel anchor not covered by uuid_extra161."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__dict__.__contains__('__repr__') == True. UUID.__repr__ returns a string of the form UUID('xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx'). '__repr__'(8 chars) IS in UUID.__dict__. uuid_extra156 anchors __repr__ via 'in' syntax but not via __contains__ under uuid162."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__dict__.__len__() == 37. The 37 keys span: 18 dunders + 1 dunder-prefix private (_from_int) + 18 non-dunder property/attribute names. uuid_extra156 anchors __len__()==37 as table rows; this spec anchors __len__()==37 as a standalone and in a combined table under uuiddict162 for fresh context."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
